member.summary: Whether to enable CMQ message notification. 1: Yes; 0: No. Only CMQ queue service is currently supported. If CMQ message notification is enabled, CloudAudit will deliver your log contents to the designated queue in the specified region in real time.

member.summary: Manages the read/write attribute of event. Valid values: 1 (read-only), 2 (write-only), 3 (read/write).

member.name: P:TencentCloud.Cloudaudit.V20190319.Models.CreateAuditRequest.AuditName
member.summary: Tracking set name, which can contain 3–128 ASCII letters (a–z; A–Z), digits (0–9), and underscores (_).

member.name: P:TencentCloud.Cloudaudit.V20190319.Models.CreateAuditRequest.CosRegion
member.summary: COS region. Supported regions can be queried through the `ListCosEnableRegion` API.

member.name: P:TencentCloud.Cloudaudit.V20190319.Models.CreateAuditRequest.IsCreateNewBucket
member.summary: Whether to create a COS bucket. 1: Yes; 0: No.

member.name: P:TencentCloud.Cloudaudit.V20190319.Models.CreateAuditRequest.CosBucketName
member.summary: User-defined COS bucket name, which can only contain 1–40 lowercase letters (a–z), digits (0–9), and dashes (-) and cannot begin or end with "-". If a bucket is not newly created, CloudAudit will not verify whether it actually exists. Enter the name with caution to avoid log delivery failure and consequent data loss.

member.name: P:TencentCloud.Cloudaudit.V20190319.Models.CreateAuditRequest.KeyId
member.summary: Globally unique ID of the CMK. This value is required if it is not a newly created KMS element. It can be obtained through `ListKeyAliasByRegion`. CloudAudit will not verify the validity of the `KeyId`. Enter it carefully to avoid data loss.

member.name: P:TencentCloud.Cloudaudit.V20190319.Models.CreateAuditRequest.CmqQueueName
member.summary: Queue name, which must begin with a letter and can contain up to 64 letters, digits, and dashes (-). This field is required if the value of `IsEnableCmqNotify` is 1. If a queue is not newly created, CloudAudit will not verify whether it actually exists. Enter the name with caution to avoid log delivery failure and consequent data loss.

member.name: P:TencentCloud.Cloudaudit.V20190319.Models.CreateAuditRequest.KmsRegion
member.summary: KMS region. Currently supported regions can be obtained through `ListKmsEnableRegion`. This must be the same as the COS region.

member.name: P:TencentCloud.Cloudaudit.V20190319.Models.CreateAuditRequest.IsEnableKmsEncry
member.summary: Whether to enable KMS encryption. 1: Yes, 0: No. If KMS encryption is enabled, the data will be encrypted when delivered to COS.

member.name: P:TencentCloud.Cloudaudit.V20190319.Models.CreateAuditRequest.CmqRegion
member.summary: Region where the queue is located. Supported CMQ regions can be queried through the `ListCmqEnableRegion` API. This field is required if the value of `IsEnableCmqNotify` is 1.

member.name: P:TencentCloud.Cloudaudit.V20190319.Models.CreateAuditRequest.LogFilePrefix
member.summary: Log file prefix, which can only contain 3–40 ASCII letters (a–z; A–Z) and digits (0–9). It can be left empty and is the account ID by default.

member.name: P:TencentCloud.Cloudaudit.V20190319.Models.CreateAuditRequest.IsCreateNewQueue
member.summary: Whether to create a queue. 1: Yes; 0: No. This field is required if the value of `IsEnableCmqNotify` is 1.
